HEADWORD: Palification
<hw>Pal`i*fi*ca"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>palus</ets> a stake + <ets>-ficare</ets> (in comp.) to make: cf. F.
<ets>palification</ets>. See <er>-fy</er>.]</ety> <def>The act or
practice of driving piles or posts into the ground to make it
firm.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Sir H. Wotton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Paliform</ent>⟦br⟧
